  "prompt": "What are good examples for new game flows for mobile apps?",
  "response": "Here are some effective game flow examples for mobile apps:\n\n1. Onboarding Flows\n- Tutorial with interactive steps\n- Quick character/avatar creation\n- Skill selection\n- Difficulty level choice\n\n2. Casual Game Flows\n- Short play sessions\n- Simple learning curve\n- Incremental challenges\n- Quick rewards/achievements\n- Social sharing options\n\n3. Progression-Based Flows\n- Level advancement\n- Skill tree unlocking\n- Character/equipment upgrades\n- Persistent progression tracking\n- Milestone rewards\n\n4. Puzzle Game Flows\n- Gradually increasing difficulty\n- Hint systems\n- Time-based challenges\n- Multiple solution paths\n- Procedural level generation\n\n5. Strategy Game Flows\n- Resource management\n- Base/team building\n- Strategic decision points\n- Multiple progression paths\n- Alliance/multiplayer interactions\n\n6. RPG-Style Flows\n- Character customization\n- Quest/mission systems\n- Narrative-driven progression\n- Experience point accumulation\n- Equipment/skill management\n\n7. Competitive Game Flows\n- Matchmaking systems\n- Ranking/leaderboard integration\n- Tournament structures\n- Skill-based matchups\n- Reward tiers\n\n8. Casual Narrative Flows\n- Interactive storytelling\n- Choice-driven narratives\n- Character relationship development\n- Multiple endings\n- Episodic content\n\n9. Idle/Incremental Game Flows\n- Passive progression\n- Automated resource generation\n- Prestige/reset mechanics\n- Continuous optimization\n- Exponential upgrades\n\n10. Social Integration Flows\n- Friend challenges\n- Collaborative missions\n- Competitive leaderboards\n- Gifting/trading mechanics\n- Social media connectivity\n\nKey Design Principles:\n- Keep initial learning curve smooth\n- Provide clear objectives\n- Offer frequent, meaningful rewards\n- Maintain engagement through variety\n- Balance challenge and accessibility",
